%S A006606 1,2,3,6,10,20,36,72,135,272,528,1048,2080,4160,8242,16500,32895,
%T A006606 65750,131328,262612,524733,1049600,2098176,4195930,8390620,16781312,
%U A006606 33558177,67116876,134225920,268450626,536887270
%N A006606 Number of nonperiodic autocorrelation functions of length n {-1,1} sequences.
%C A006606 The nonperiodic autocorrelation function of a length n sequence A = (a_0,a_1,a_2,...,a_{n-1}) is defined as NPAF(A) = (b_1,b_2,...,b_{n-1}) where b_k = Sum_{i=0..n-k-1} a_i * a_{i+k}. - _John Tyler Rascoe_, May 08 2026
%D A006606 N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
%D A006606 E. G. Whitehead, Jr., Autocorrelation of (+1,-1) sequences, pp. 329-336 of Combinatorial Mathematics (Canberra, 1977), Lect. Notes Math. 686, 1978. [From Jayadev Acharya (jayadev(AT)ucsd.edu), Aug 20 2009]
%H A006606 Michael Pohl, <a href="https://scholarship.richmond.edu/honors-theses/205">Crossover property of the nonperiodic autocorrelation of quaternary sequences</a>, Honors Thesis, University of Richmond, 2007.
%H A006606 E. G. Whitehead, Jr., <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BFb0062549">Autocorrelation of (+1,-1) sequences</a>, In: Holton, D.A., Seberry, J. (eds) Combinatorial Mathematics. Lecture Notes in Mathematics, vol 686. Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg.
%e A006606 The {-1,1} sequence of length 4, A = (1,-1,1,1) has the nonperiodic autocorrelation function NPAF(A) = (-1, 0, 1), so this is one distinct NPAF counted under a(4) = 6. - _John Tyler Rascoe_, May 08 2026
%Y A006606 Cf. A000079, A045690.
